blicans-attack-biden-with-a-fully-ai-generated-ad-184055192.html">人工智能生成的攻击广告</a>而受到批评，而三星员工据称在使用该机器人工作时通过 ChatGPT <a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/three-samsung-employees-reportedly-leaked-sensitive-data-to-chatgpt-190221114.html">泄露了敏感数据</a>。由于<a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/chatgpt-openai-new-york-city-public-schools-ban-192608080.html">担心作弊，</a>学校已禁止使用这些系统。理论上，住房限制可以防止类似的问题，例如人工智能撰写的立法和演讲。</p><p>众议院的政策可能不会面临太多反对。国会双方都在试图规范和管理人工智能。在众议院，众议员 Ritchie Torries <a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.axios.com/2023/06/03/house-democrats-ritchie-torres-ai-disclosure">提出了</a>一项法案，要求对生成人工智能的使用提供免责声明，而众议员 Yvette Clark 希望<a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/house-bill-would-demand-disclosure-of-ai-generated-content-in-political-ads-190524733.html">对政治广告进行类似的披露</a>。参议员们就人工智能问题举行了听证会，并提出了一项法案， <a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/senate-bill-would-hold-ai-companies-liable-for-harmful-content-212340911.html">要求人工智能开发人员对使用其平台产生的有害内容负责</a>。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/congress-is-reportedly-limiting-staff-use-of-ai-models-like-chatgpt-195454777.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/congress-is-reportedly-limiting-staff-use-of-ai-models-like-chatgpt-195454777.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 42348359-76c7-4bac-8865-8f0f2296e748</guid><dc:creator>乔恩·芬加斯</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Mon, 26 Jun 2023 19:54:54 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1687831992</ingested><modified> 2023-06-27T02:13:15+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Jon Fingas]]></category><media:content height="2624" medium="image" url="https